(50, 1, '2016-11-18 16:59:29', '2016-11-18 16:59:29', '<h4 class="title">Robotizens: LEGO Robotics Camps and Classes for the Bay Area</h4>\r\n							<br/><br/>\r\n                            <p>Robotizens is a LEGO Mindstorms-based program in the in which children (ages 8-12) will work hands-on with the latest generation of LEGO Robotics and work with various FLL Challenges. We offer a beginner/intermediate level Robotizens program that uses past FLL challenges.</p>\r\n<p>Students work in small teams and build a variety of robot projects using LEGO Mindstorms. These projects provide an opportunity to study construction methods, principles of physics and science and basic concepts of engineering, such as connected systems, motorized machines, levers, gears, pulleys, speed/torque, stress testing, and more.  The students will learn how to program the robots to perform tasks, use sensors, and solve a series of fun challenges.</p>\r\n<p>Please visit our Fall program page for further information on scheduling and class calendar for Fall 2014.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, we are also putting together two teams this Fall that will compete in the FLL challenge. The weekly meetings will take place at our Los Altos and Saratoga locations. The exact schedule will be posted shortly. If you’re interested in participating in the Los Altos or Saratoga FLL team, please send us an email at info@kidzzinc.com.</p>', 'Robotizens', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'robotizens', '', '', '2016-12-14 11:40:56', '2016-12-14 11:40:56', '', 11, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/?page_id=50', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(51, 1, '2016-11-18 16:59:29', '2016-11-18 16:59:29', '', 'Robotizens', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '50-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-18 16:59:29', '2016-11-18 16:59:29', '', 50, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/18/50-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(52, 1, '2016-11-18 17:00:07', '2016-11-18 17:00:07', '<h4 class="title">LEGO Social Skills Program</h4>\r\n							<br/><br/>\r\n                            <p>Do you love LEGOs and want to practice making friends and working collaboratively in a safe, structured, and FUN learning environment? Then, join our ‘LEGO Social Skills Club!’ Kidizens is proud to offer a special class for children with social challenges who would benefit from explicit teaching about social skills and social thinking (kids who may have social delays, kids with ASD, or 2E kids). Like our traditional Kidizens program, they will plan and construct a city together in a specially adapted, cooperative learning program designed to also promote social learning and reinforce positive social behaviors, while leveraging many of the successful elements of our regular Kidizens program.</p>\r\n<h5>Spring 2016</h5>\r\n<p>Over the course of the program, the kids will partner up to plan a component of our city and direct the class in building. In addition to being individually responsible for overseeing their special projects, kidizens will have many opportunities to hone their public speaking skills in a structured and non-threatening environment. Each session also will incorporate activities to foster emotional intelligence and help kidizens express themselves effectively. Join us, as a part of this social skills club, as we construct our self-designed city, build healthy social relationships, and of course, have tons of LEGO fun!</p>\r\n<p>Please note that this program is meant to nurture project-based and group learning in a collaborative, fun, social environment for kids with social delays or challenges. We’re not a “therapy” program and not equipped to handle kids with any known history of violence and aggression. We’ll also be scheduling a group observation during the first couple of classes to assess a fit for all the kids that are registered for this class.</p>\r\n<p>These classes will be taught by our experienced teacher, Kimberly Eng Lee, with significant experience in teaching social skills and social thinking to special needs kids.</p>\r\n<p>Please contact us if you’re interested in joining or forming a social skills group at Kidizens. We offer quite a bit of flexibility in scheduling a session that’s appropriate for you. If you’re a homeschooling group of 5 kids or more, we can schedule a class at a convenient time this Spring, based on our current schedule.</p>', 'LEGO Social Skills', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lego-social-skills', '', '', '2016-12-14 11:50:16', '2016-12-14 11:50:16', '', 11, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/?page_id=52', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(53, 1, '2016-11-18 17:00:07', '2016-11-18 17:00:07', '', 'LEGO Social Skills', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '52-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-18 17:00:07', '2016-11-18 17:00:07', '', 52, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/18/52-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(54, 1, '2016-11-18 17:00:41', '2016-11-18 17:00:41', '<h4 class="title">Drop-In Sessions</h4>\r\n							<br/><br/>\r\n                            <p>Kidizens now offers group drop-in sessions for you to schedule a fun LEGO play session for your child or a group playdate for your child and their friends!  Gather your child and four or more of his/her friends together to build anything that suits their imagination, a small city, a city of skyscrapers or even a space colony.  Pick topics from our  numerous fun themes that will stimulate the group.</p>\r\n<p>If you would like to schedule or plan a group Drop-in Session, please email us at info@kidzzinc.com. The cost per child is $18/ hour (or $34 for 2 hours).</p>\r\n<p>Our drop-in sessions start the week of Sep 12th for Fall at all our locations and are scheduled as follows until Dec 16th (No sessions on Friday, Nov 25th) after thanksgiving):</p>\r\n<p>You will need to email/call us in order to confirm the availability of a drop-in session or to reserve a slot in advance.</p>', 'Drop-In Sessions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'drop-in-sessions', '', '', '2016-12-14 11:51:10', '2016-12-14 11:51:10', '', 11, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/?page_id=54', 0, 'page', '', 0),
