(156, 1, '2016-11-20 03:42:02', '2016-11-20 03:42:02', '<p>At Kidizens, we are building responsible, future leaders, one brick, one project, one city at a time. Our mission is to cultivate creative, critical and civically responsible thinking that can be the foundational pillar of future learning in life. We believe that the Kidizens, network of cities cultivates a deep understanding of how societies function and evolve.</p>\r\n                            <p><b>Build, Learn, Lead, One Brick at a Time.</b><br/>\r\n								Would you like to leverage your love of LEGOs to learn real-life skills and strategies?\r\n							</p>\r\n							<p>For children, ages 6 and up, who love LEGOs and are looking for new opportunities to collaborate with peers in a fun and interactive social learning environment, we offer Kidizens.</p>\r\n							<p>Kidizens is an innovative educational environment where students build, inhabit, manage and govern their own LEGO city. We encourage collaborative and guided discovery of real-world concepts while role-playing and having fun in a universe built of LEGOs.</p>\r\n							<p>The guiding principle of the Kidizens program is to offer a highly immersive, experiential learning environment for kids that nurtures their creative confidence and design thinking skills. We believe that when kids are engaged in a project that they find meaningful and exciting, their desire for knowledge is limitless.  Research has shown that students recall 20% of what they hear but as much as 90% of what they have the opportunity to "experience" or do.</p>\r\n							<p>At Kidizens, we combine experiential learning with detailed civics, history and real-life lessons to create a fun LEGO environment that encourages students to let their imaginations take them to new heights. In designing, building, and governing an interactive LEGO society, our kidizens are truly engaged as stakeholders and motivated to learn about everything from the intricacies of a city council meeting to the importance of managing a budget. Along the way, they learn important skills, such as problem-solving, decision making, conflict resolution, public speaking and leadership.</p>\r\n                            <p>The goal is simple: Inspire our students to develop the skills they need to become the good citizens and civically aware and responsible future leaders of tomorrow.</p>\r\n							<p>We also offer in-school and customized workshops, birthday parties, and drop-in sessions to supplement our standard program offerings.</p>\r\n							<p>\r\n								<b>Parents and Students Love Kidizens</b><br/>Take our virtual tour to learn more about the Kidizens program and watch a testimonial video to hear what parents and students have to say about their experience.\r\n							</p>\r\n							<p>\r\n								Kidizens is based in California and you can contact us to schedule a visit or speak with us. We are happy to answer any questions you may have about Kidizens.\r\n							</p>\r\n', 'About Kidizens', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '7-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-20 03:42:02', '2016-11-20 03:42:02', '', 7, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/20/7-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(157, 1, '2017-01-12 12:10:04', '2017-01-12 12:10:04', '<p class="content-img"> Now experience the creativity, satisfaction and excitement of building a city on your special day…..Be the Mayor, help your friends build a city, or just let your imagination take you on a guided discovery…. It is truly an exciting and unique way to mark a birthday, especially for all the LEGO-lovers!</p>\n<p><b>We are now taking reservations for Birthday parties, at our newest Saratoga location! Please email <a class="linkto" href="mailto:info@kidzzinc.com">info@kidzzinc.com</a> if you have any questions or to reserve a spot.</b></p>\n<h4>LEGO Birthday Fun for All Ages</h4><br/><br/>\n<p class="content-img listing"><img src="http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/lego-birthday-party-2.jpg" draggable="false" alt="kidizens lego birthday party"> When your child hosts a birthday party at Kidizens, it isn’t just a day of celebration, it is a  jam-packed day of creativity and excitement.  During the party, the birthday child and his/her friends build an entire LEGO city while making important decisions – the birthday child gets to name the city or an important landmark in the city. By the end of the party the children create something of which they can truly be proud.</p>\n<p>We provide a huge LEGO inventory, creative environment and endless fun!</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> You bring your own party supplies, cake, food and decorations.</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Our party coordinator will supervise and guide all the building activities.</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> We have mini-figures, candies and small LEGO sets to purchase as party favors.</p>\n<h4>Birthday Party FAQ</h4>\n<p class="content-img listing"><img src="http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/lego-birthday-party-3.jpg" draggable="false" alt="kidizens lego birthday party"> We now offer birthday parties for different age groups (from ages 5 to 14) at our locations in Los Altos, Saratoga and Belmont.\nWe offer many kinds of parties with varied themes (the theme could vary depending upon the Birthday child’s interests, total number of children and total time for the party). We often tweak the theme to customize it your child’s interest and to make the experience unique. There are a number of interesting options:</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Rival Town: Build an entire city to rival an existing Kidizens LEGO city</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Star Wars and Space-related themes</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Race Cars (integrating Robotic elements)</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Transportation – trains, buses, airplanes, ships</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Baseball League: Perfect party for the birthday child who loves LEGOs as well as baseball</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Build Landmarks and monuments around the world</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Build a LEGO castle or a “sky-high” tower (more suitable for younger kids)</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Contest Mania: Design contests involving themes that match the party or Birthday child’s interests</p>\n<p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Or Build Anything from Your Own Wild Imagination!</p>\n<p><img src="http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/lego-birthday-party-5.jpg" draggable="false" alt="kidizens lego birthday party"></p> \n<div class="listing">\n<b>How many children can participate?</b>\nWe have found that you need at least 8-10 children to generate enough excitement and energy and to make a successful party. The maximum number of kids for a party is 25.\n<b>How much do you charge?</b>\nPrices depend upon the location, the length of the party and number of children. We do charge a minimum of $250 per party. Please refer to our pricing page for more guidelines.\n<b>Does the party work well for girls?</b>\nYes, all our projects are geared for girls and boys and are lot of fun for any creative child and/or LEGO builder.\n<p><b>How long does the party last?</b>\nOur parties are 2 hours long. There is a built-in window to allow all guests to arrive before starting the activity and there is also time built in for celebration and cake-cutting at the end. Our party coordinators make a presentation to help all kids immerse in the birthday theme and simulate fun events throughout the party to make it really engaging a lot of fun!!</p>\n<p><b>Do you offer parties on weekdays?</b>\nWe do offer parties on select Friday afternoons, if scheduled sufficiently, at least a month, in advance.</p>\n<p><b>Do the participants get to keep any of the LEGO bricks?</b>\nThe participants don’t get to keep any of the bricks, but what the kids create is likely to live on in each child’s memories and photographs for a long time!</p>\n<h5>Contact Kidizens to Schedule Your Lego Themed Birthday Party Today</h5>\n<p>Ready to help your child create LEGO birthday memories that will last a lifetime – Please contact us for specific details and to schedule a party.</p>\n<p>We are currently looking for a Birthday Party Coordinator for our Saratoga Location.</p>\n</div>', 'Birthday Parties', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 12:10:04', '2017-01-12 12:10:04', '', 13, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/20/13-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(193, 1, '2016-11-22 16:52:22', '2016-11-22 16:52:22', '<h4>Schools Offering Kidizens After-School LEGO Classes in Fall.</h4>\r\n<p>Kidizens is proud to partner with select schools in the Bay Area that embrace project-based learning philosophies to offer a variety of Kidizens workshops that combine civic and economic learning with LEGO fun for students. Our Fall 2016 workshops are:</p>\r\n<h5>Keys School Kidizens Young Entrepreneurs Workshop</h5> \r\n<p>The workshop will have kids creatively thinking, designing, planning and launching businesses. The workshop will then teach the basics of managing a business with LEGO-based prototypes. Each child will design, build, budget and manage a business of their choice.  In this context, we will discuss economic concepts such as budgets, loans, profits and overhead, as the Young Entrepreneurs will use their ingenuity and acumen to make their businesses appealing to customers resulting in successful, profitable ventures. In addition, they will serve on a citywide council to manage policy making for the city which may have the potential to affect their businesses. The session will end with the children sharing their businesses in a ‘Shark Tank’ style presentation.</p>\r\n', 'After-School Workshops', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'after-school-workshops', '', '', '2016-12-14 12:22:58', '2016-12-14 12:22:58', '', 56, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/?page_id=193', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(158, 1, '2016-11-20 04:16:57', '2016-11-20 04:16:57', '          <p><b>At our Fall/ Winter workshops the kids are age-appropriately partnered to build cities and solve civic/economic problems and take decisions to form a well functioning society. The kids face a few challenges along the way and end the workshop evaluating city economy and overall citizen happiness, in addition to putting some laws and services in place â€” and of course, having lots of fun while doing so!</b></p>\r\n							<h5>1-Day Holiday Workshops</h5>\r\n							\r\n                            <p>Offered on staff development days, school holidays or in-service days. For list of additional workshops, please see the schedule below. Our 1-day workshops feature unique, immersive themes â€“ including city building, space exploration or an explorer, gold rush experience!</p>\r\n							\r\n							<h5>Thanksgiving 2-day Workshops: Nov 21st-22nd</h5>\r\n							\r\n                            <p>2-day workshops where the kids think, plan and build cities, while solving many problems along the way.<br/>\r\nOffered at all our locations: Nov 21st â€“ 22nd from 9am to 3:00pm;<br/>\r\nAfter-care available until 5pm</p>\r\n\r\n							<h5>Winter Camps: Dec 19th-21st and Dec 28th â€“ 30th; 9am to 3:00pm</h5>\r\n							\r\n                            <p>3-day winter workshops where the kids immerse themselves a bit deeper in the cities they build, solve civic/economic problems and take decisions to form a well functioning society.<br/>\r\nOffered at all our locations: Dec 19th-21st and Dec 28th-30th, from 9am to 3:00pm; After-care available until 5pm</p>\r\n							\r\n							<h6>Registration is now open for all of these workshops. In addition, check out our special drop-in sessions if you want to spend a part of the day with us or please contact us if you would like to schedule an extended, customized drop-in session with a group of kids. Many drop-in sessions available during the holidays.</h6>\r\n							<br/>\r\n							<p><b>Pl send us an email at info@kidzzinc.com, if youâ€™re looking for a particular holiday camp and donâ€™t see it listed here. Thanks!</b></p>\r\n', 'Birthday Parties', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-20 04:16:57', '2016-11-20 04:16:57', '', 13, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/20/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(159, 1, '2016-11-20 04:17:49', '2016-11-20 04:17:49', '<h4 class="title">Kidizens Fall/Winter 2016 LEGO Camps and Workshops</h4>          \r\n<p><b>At our Fall/ Winter workshops the kids are age-appropriately partnered to build cities and solve civic/economic problems and take decisions to form a well functioning society. The kids face a few challenges along the way and end the workshop evaluating city economy and overall citizen happiness, in addition to putting some laws and services in place â€” and of course, having lots of fun while doing so!</b></p>\r\n							<h5>1-Day Holiday Workshops</h5>\r\n							\r\n                            <p>Offered on staff development days, school holidays or in-service days. For list of additional workshops, please see the schedule below. Our 1-day workshops feature unique, immersive themes â€“ including city building, space exploration or an explorer, gold rush experience!</p>\r\n							\r\n							<h5>Thanksgiving 2-day Workshops: Nov 21st-22nd</h5>\r\n							\r\n                            <p>2-day workshops where the kids think, plan and build cities, while solving many problems along the way.<br/>\r\nOffered at all our locations: Nov 21st â€“ 22nd from 9am to 3:00pm;<br/>\r\nAfter-care available until 5pm</p>\r\n\r\n							<h5>Winter Camps: Dec 19th-21st and Dec 28th â€“ 30th; 9am to 3:00pm</h5>\r\n							\r\n                            <p>3-day winter workshops where the kids immerse themselves a bit deeper in the cities they build, solve civic/economic problems and take decisions to form a well functioning society.<br/>\r\nOffered at all our locations: Dec 19th-21st and Dec 28th-30th, from 9am to 3:00pm; After-care available until 5pm</p>\r\n							\r\n							<h6>Registration is now open for all of these workshops. In addition, check out our special drop-in sessions if you want to spend a part of the day with us or please contact us if you would like to schedule an extended, customized drop-in session with a group of kids. Many drop-in sessions available during the holidays.</h6>\r\n							<br/>\r\n							<p><b>Pl send us an email at info@kidzzinc.com, if youâ€™re looking for a particular holiday camp and donâ€™t see it listed here. Thanks!</b></p>\r\n', 'Birthday Parties', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-20 04:17:49', '2016-11-20 04:17:49', '', 13, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/20/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
