(175, 1, '2016-11-22 05:04:11', '2016-11-22 05:04:11', '<p>“Tell me, and I will forget. Show me, and I may remember. Involve me, and I will understand.” – Confucius 450 BC</p>\r\n<p>Kidizens has created our innovative education based on years of research pointing to the benefits of experiential learning. Watch our virtual tour or read what students and their parents have to say and you’ll know our programs produce happy kids. But the true benefit in Kidizens lies in the deep learning that takes place while the students are having all that fun.</p>\r\n<p>Kidizens combines key insights from experiential learning researchers with years of successful LEGO learning programs to create a system that inspires students to learn.\r\nHere are just a few of the studies and research reports that show why innovative experience-based programs, like Kidizens, produce results:</p>\r\n<div class="research-page">\r\n<h5>Experiential Learning:</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://learningfromexperience.com/">http://learningfromexperience.com/</a>\r\n“Nothing ever becomes real till it is experienced — even a proverb is no proverb to you till your life has illustrated it.” –John Keats (1795-1821)\r\n</p>\r\n<h5>Whole Child Learning:</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://www.wholechildeducation.org/">http://www.wholechildeducation.org/</a>\r\n“The greatest sign of success for a teacher… is to be able to say, “The children are now working as if I did not exist.” – Maria Montessori\r\n</p>\r\n<h5>LEGO Learning Institute:</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://learninginstitute.lego.com/en-us/Default.aspx">http://learninginstitute.lego.com/en-us/Default.aspx</a>\r\n“I never teach my pupils. I only attempt to provide the conditions in which they can learn.”— Albert Einstein\r\n</p>\r\n<h5>Scholars Put Civics in the Same Category as Literacy, Math: </h5>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://www.edweek.org/ew/articles/2011/10/26/09civics.h31.html?tkn=SNYF5LTuKGxUmYpK78YHv7MDI7wRZhBHcLnF&intc=es">http://www.edweek.org/ew/articles/2011/10/26/09civics.h31.html?tkn=SNYF5LTuKGxUmYpK78YHv7MDI7wRZhBHcLnF&intc=es</a>\r\n“Nothing ever becomes real till it is experienced — even a proverb is no proverb to you till your life has illustrated it.” –John Keats (1795-1821)\r\n</p>\r\n<h5>The Learning Power of LEGO:    </h5>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://learninginstitute.lego.com/en-us/Default.aspx">http://learninginstitute.lego.com/en-us/Default.aspx</a>\r\n“I never teach my pupils. I only attempt to provide the conditions in which they can learn.”— Albert Einstein\r\n</p>\r\n<h5>LEGO Learning Institute:</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://www.onlinecollege.org/2012/01/30/the-learning-power-of-lego/">http://www.onlinecollege.org/2012/01/30/the-learning-power-of-lego/</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<h5>Our Partner, The Synapse School, Points Out the Value of EQ:</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://synapseschool.org/curriculum/emotional-intelligence/">http://synapseschool.org/curriculum/emotional-intelligence/</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<h5>We Love the Educational Philsophy Exhibited at Stanford’s K12 Laboratory:</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://dschool.stanford.edu/k12/research.php">http://dschool.stanford.edu/k12/research.php</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>“10 papers released by the American Enterprise Institute last week make the case that civics education is as critical as literacy and mathematics”– Jaclyn Zubrzycki</p>\r\n<p>Fun Links to Social Studies Pages!</p>\r\n<h5>The First Car – A History of the Automobile</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.ausbcomp.com">www.ausbcomp.com</a></p>\r\n<h5>Time For Kids</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.timeforkids.com">www.timeforkids.com</a></p>\r\n<h5>The One Room Schoolhouse</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.oneroomschoolhouses.ca">www.oneroomschoolhouses.ca</a></p>\r\n<h5>NASA – NASA Kids’ Club</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nasa.gov">www.nasa.gov</a></p>\r\n<h5>Then/Now – Series – The New York Times</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://topics.nytimes.com">topics.nytimes.com</a></p>\r\n<h5>The First Car – Scholastic Kids Press Corps | News for Kids, By Kids</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://teacher.scholastic.com">teacher.scholastic.com</a></p>\r\n<h5>Kids in the House – Young Learners</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://kids.clerk.house.gov">kids.clerk.house.gov</a></p>\r\n<h5>WayBack . Technology 1900 | PBS KIDS GO!\r\npbskids.org\r\nKIDS AGAINST GLOBAL WARMING</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.alligatorboogaloo.com">www.alligatorboogaloo.com</a></p>\r\n<h5>Big Apple History | PBS KIDS GO!</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://pbskids.org/bigapplehistory/index-flash.html">http://pbskids.org/bigapplehistory/index-flash.html</a></p>\r\n<h5>White House 101 | The White House</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov">www.whitehouse.gov</a></p>\r\n<h5>America by Air</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.nasm.si.edu">www.nasm.si.edu</a></p>\r\n<h5>Congress for Kids – Interactive, Fun-filled Experiences About the Federal Government</h5>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.congressforkids.net">www.congressforkids.net</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Drop by a Kidizens class to see the benefits or select a program that is appropriate for your child and register today.</p>', 'Research', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'research', '', '', '2016-12-14 07:36:21', '2016-12-14 07:36:21', '', 23, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/?page_id=175', 0, 'page', '', 0),
