(228, 1, '2016-11-23 12:41:30', '2016-11-23 12:41:30', ' <h4 class="title">Learn to play. Play to learn. Learn to Lead.</h4>\n							<br/><br/>\n                            <p>We continue to be excited about our Young Kidizens program as a perfect beginning to the Kidizens program.  Our unique constructivist framework of city-building, role-playing and social learning enables groups of younger students to take on a guided discovery of real-life concepts.  While the overall concept and experiential learning philosophy of Kidizens runs through all problems, our curriculum for the “Young Kidizens,” is designed specifically for the target age group of 6-7 (and young 8’s), with the goal of simplifying many civic and economic concepts and bringing them to life with many play-based elements.</p>\n							<p>\n							<h5>Overview:</h5>\n							<p>14-week highly interactive and fun session</p>\n                            <p>Targeted at Ages 6 – Young 8-yr olds – Students attend one session a week. For our Kinders – we now offer Kinderzens – please see description below.</p>\n							<p>Students build their own entire LEGO city and interact with each other while learning simple real-world civics concepts, lessons and social skills.</p>\n							<p>\n							Teachers guide young kids in a primarily play-based learning environment\n							</p>\n							<p>\n							Kids build various infrastructure projects – police station, fire station, hospitals, schools, airport, explore transportation options and much more.\n							</p>\n							<p>\n							Kids study “real-life” versions of each building before beginning their own LEGO versions.  They will find out just what a “day in the life” of a fire fighter, police officer or doctor entails through various events and interactions with their city.\n							</p>\n							<p>\n							Kids meet and role play as a City Council to discuss issues and run for elections for various jobs. It’s going to be a big responsibility on the little shoulders!\n							</p>\n							<p>\nIn all, the kids will explore, build, have fun, and interact in a socially rich environment, without even realizing that they are continually learning the everyday important lessons of life.							</p>\n							<div class="listing">\n							<p><b>Los Altos Fall YK Classes (Serving Palo Alto, Los Altos and Mountain View areas):</b><br/><b>Homeschooling Options:</b></p>\n							<p>Wednesday      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  10:30 AM – 12:15 PM<br/>\n								Friday        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    10:00 AM – 11:45 AM\n							</p>\n							<p><b>After-School Options:</b></p>\n							<p>Tuesday        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  3:30 PM – 5:15 PM <br/>\n							Wednesday        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   3:30 PM – 5:15 PM\n							</p>\n							<a href="#" class="register-button">Register</a>\n							</div>\n							<div class="listing">\n							<p><b>Saratoga Classes (Serving Cupertino, Saratoga, Los Gatos and Santa Clara areas):</b><br/><b>Homeschooling Options:</b></p>\n							<p>Tuesday      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  10:00 AM – 11:45 AM<br/>\n								Thursday       &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    10:00 AM – 12:30 PM\n							</p>\n							<p><b>After-School Options:</b></p>\n							<p>Monday         &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  3:30 PM -5:15 PM<br/>\n								Tuesday       &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    3:30 PM -5:15PM\n							</p>\n							<a href="#" class="register-button">Register</a>\n							</div>\n							<div class="listing">\n							<p><b>Belmont Fall YK Classes (Serving Belmont, San Carlos, San Mateo, Foster City and Redwood City areas): </b><br/><b>Homeschooling Options:</b></p>\n							<p>Tuesday      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  10:00 AM – 11:45 AM<br/>\n								Thursday       &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    10:00 AM – 12:30 PM\n							</p>\n							<p><b>After-School Options:</b></p>\n							<p>Monday         &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  3:30 PM -5:15 PM<br/>\n								Wednesday       &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    2:00 PM -3:45PM\n							</p>\n							<a href="#" class="register-button">Register</a>\n							</div>\n							<h5>Dates:</h5>\n                            <p>Our Fall Semester kicks off on Tuesday, Sep 6th 2016 and ends on Friday, December 16th. We’re off during the week of Thanksgiving (tue-thu) and offer special-themed workshops during those days.</p>\n							<h5>Register:</h5>\n                            <p>Please email us at info@kidzzinc.com to reserve a spot for the day you would like to register for. Our online registration would be open soon.</p>\n							<p> *In addition to our regularly scheduled Fall classes, we can put together a 12-14 week customized session for homeschooling groups, special workshops, and Girls’ and Boy’s scout clubs as per the convenience of their schedules. Please email us at info@kidzzinc.com.</p>\n							<h5>Pricing:</h5>\n                            <p>See our Pricing Page for more details or contact us.</p>', 'Young kidizens fall', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '197-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-11-23 12:41:30', '2016-11-23 12:41:30', '', 197, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/23/197-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
