(539, 1, '2017-01-12 15:51:00', '2017-01-12 15:51:00', '<br/><br/>\r\n							<h4 class="title">Enjoy a night out on the town while your children engage in a Kidizens LEGO universe!</h4>\r\n                            <p>Kidizens Kids’ Night Out offers a fun and unique experience for parents and children alike. Parents can enjoy some time to themselves, while the children immerse themselves in building and exploring an entire LEGO universe spanning Ninjago, Chima, Superheroes, Star Wars, Minecraft, Pokemons and much more, while having loads of fun!</p>\r\n							<h4>Event Information:</h4>\r\n                            <p><b>Snacks provided. Highly interactive and collaborative experience.  Age range: 6-12</b>\r\n							</p>\r\n							<h4>Held at our Los Altos Location every month!</h4><br/><br/>\r\n<h4>Stay tuned for our next date!</h4><br/><br/>\r\n							<p>If interested or need more information, please contact us at <a href="#" style="color:#80cd33">info@kidzzinc.com.</a></p>', 'Kids Night Out New', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '30-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 15:51:00', '2017-01-12 15:51:00', '', 30, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2017/01/12/30-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(262, 1, '2016-11-24 09:29:25', '2016-11-24 09:29:25', '<h4 class="title">Kids’ Night Out Camp</h4>\r\n							<br/><br/>\r\n							<h4 class="title">Enjoy a night out on the town while your children engage in a Kidizens LEGO universe!</h4>\r\n                            <p>Kidizens Kids’ Night Out offers a fun and unique experience for parents and children alike. Parents can enjoy some time to themselves, while the children immerse themselves in building and exploring an entire LEGO universe spanning Ninjago, Chima, Superheroes, Star Wars, Minecraft, Pokemons and much more, while having loads of fun!</p>\r\n							<h4>Event Information:</h4>\r\n                            <p><b>Snacks provided. Highly interactive and collaborative experience.  Age range: 6-12</b>\r\n							</p>\r\n							<h4>Held at our Los Altos Location every month!</h4>\r\n							<br/>\r\n							<p><b>October 14th, 6:00pm-9:00pm Cost: $60</b></p>\r\n							<a href="#" class="register-button">REGISTER</a>\r\n							<p>If you have any questions please contact us at <a href="#" style="color:#80cd33">info@kidzzinc.com.</a></p>', 'Kids Night Out New', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '30-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-24 09:29:25', '2016-11-24 09:29:25', '', 30, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/24/30-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(411, 1, '2016-12-14 07:00:22', '2016-12-14 07:00:22', '<p>At Kidizens, we believe in the benefits of encouraging experiential learning that engages the whole child. Our students learn by exploring, experiencing and addressing real-life situations. They build to think, explore, and act!</p>\r\n<h4>Kidizens Build to Learn and Lead</h4>\r\n<p>In our classes, students develop cities from the ground up and follow a detailed curriculum, where “kid citizens” take on roles such as mayor, sheriff, city planner, ambassador and more. They work with each other to determine the kind of city governance required and solve problems as they mange and govern their own cities.</p>\r\n<p>They discover the need for cities to provide for public safety, write laws, and pass legislation that takes into account and balances the often divergent wishes of other kidizens. And in this fun and social environment, they learn about social studies, civics, history, economics, money management, architecture, the environment, problem solving, writing, public speaking and much more.</p>\r\n<h4>A Curriculum-Based Approach</h4>\r\n<p>Although, there’s a lot of creativity inherent to the program, Kidizens follows an in-depth curriculum to delivering its lessons. We have an in-depth library of civics and social studies lessons (more than 100 highly interactive lessons) on all topics ranging from constitutions to need for insurance and political campaign strategies! The teachers acting as facilitators pick the lesson that is needed, given the dynamically changing situations in every classroom, dictated by the social interactions and city council decisions of the children.</p>\r\n<h4>Common Core Standards</h4>\r\n<p>There is fundamental shift in the way of imparting education – it is to prepare the kids of today for the needs of tomorrow. As educators around the world recognize the value of real-world learning and readiness for 21st century skills, they are embracing newer forms of teaching/learning and are adopting new education standards.</p>\r\n<p>Hands-on projects are at the cornerstone of 21st century classrooms, and are being introduced as part of this new project-based learning. This new insurgence of outside-the-box thinking as it pertains to our children’s education, comes to us in the form of new standards, being adopted and implemented throughout the country.</p>\r\n<p>The newly adopted Common Core Standards are a set of guidelines that will answer the need for teaching children the skills needed in the 21st century. <b>This collaborative, creative, self-directed learning, that involves critical thinking and deep problem solving every step along the way, is quintessential to all of our programs at Kidizens!</b></p>', 'Learning Philosophy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '23-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-14 07:00:22', '2016-12-14 07:00:22', '', 23, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/12/14/23-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(264, 1, '2016-11-24 09:32:50', '2016-11-24 09:32:50', '<h4 class="title">LEGO Fall and Winter Camps</h4>\r\n							<br/><br/>\r\n							<h4 class="title">Kidizens Fall/Winter 2016 LEGO Camps and Workshops</h4>\r\n                            <p><b>At our Fall/ Winter workshops the kids are age-appropriately partnered to build cities and solve civic/economic problems and take decisions to form a well functioning society. The kids face a few challenges along the way and end the workshop evaluating city economy and overall citizen happiness, in addition to putting some laws and services in place — and of course, having lots of fun while doing so!</b></p>\r\n							<h5>1-Day Holiday Workshops</h5>\r\n<p>Offered on staff development days, school holidays or in-service days. For list of additional workshops, please see the schedule below. Our 1-day workshops feature unique, immersive themes – including city building, space exploration or an explorer, gold rush experience!</p>\r\n					<h5>Thanksgiving 2-day Workshops: Nov 21st-22nd</h5>\r\n			<p>2-day workshops where the kids think, plan and build cities, while solving many problems along the way.<br/>\r\nOffered at all our locations: Nov 21st – 22nd from 9am to 3:00pm;<br/>\r\nAfter-care available until 5pm</p>\r\n<h5>Winter Camps: Dec 19th-21st and Dec 28th – 30th; 9am to 3:00pm</h5>\r\n<p>3-day winter workshops where the kids immerse themselves a bit deeper in the cities they build, solve civic/economic problems and take decisions to form a well functioning society.<br/>\r\nOffered at all our locations: Dec 19th-21st and Dec 28th-30th, from 9am to 3:00pm; After-care available until 5pm</p>\r\n<h6>Registration is now open for all of these workshops. In addition, check out our special drop-in sessions if you want to spend a part of the day with us or please contact us if you would like to schedule an extended, customized drop-in session with a group of kids. Many drop-in sessions available during the holidays.</h6>\r\n							<br/>\r\n							<p><b>Pl send us an email at info@kidzzinc.com, if you’re looking for a particular holiday camp and don’t see it listed here. Thanks!</b></p>', 'LEGO Fall and Winter Camps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-24 09:32:50', '2016-11-24 09:32:50', '', 32, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/24/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(266, 1, '2016-11-24 09:36:01', '2016-11-24 09:36:01', '<h4 class="title">Kidizens Spring Camps and Workshops</h4>\r\n                            <p><b>Our Kidizens Spring program is ending on May 24th, 2016. We have had another successful session full of real-life learning and discoveries. Please check out our Fall 2016 program if you’re interested in joining our journey as ''kidizens''.</b></p>\r\n							<p>\r\n								Check out our special drop-in sessions if you want to spend a part of the day with us or please contact us if you would like to schedule an extended, customized drop-in session with a group of kids. Many drop-in sessions available during the holidays. In addition, if you’re looking for a particular holiday camp and don’t see it listed here, send us an email at info@kidzzinc.com.\r\n							</p>', 'LEGO Spring Camps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '34-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-24 09:36:01', '2016-11-24 09:36:01', '', 34, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/24/34-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(265, 1, '2016-11-24 09:35:31', '2016-11-24 09:35:31', '<h4 class="title">LEGO Spring Camps</h4>\r\n							<br/><br/>\r\n							<h4 class="title">Kidizens Spring Camps and Workshops</h4>\r\n                            <p><b>Our Kidizens Spring program is ending on May 24th, 2016. We have had another successful session full of real-life learning and discoveries. Please check out our Fall 2016 program if you’re interested in joining our journey as ''kidizens''.</b></p>\r\n							<p>\r\n								Check out our special drop-in sessions if you want to spend a part of the day with us or please contact us if you would like to schedule an extended, customized drop-in session with a group of kids. Many drop-in sessions available during the holidays. In addition, if you’re looking for a particular holiday camp and don’t see it listed here, send us an email at info@kidzzinc.com.\r\n							</p>', 'LEGO Spring Camps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '34-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-24 09:35:31', '2016-11-24 09:35:31', '', 34, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/24/34-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(267, 1, '2016-11-24 09:37:44', '2016-11-24 09:37:44', '<h4 class="title">Kidizens Lego Summer Camps for the Bay Area</h4>\r\n                            <p><b>Would you like to build and be the Mayor of an entire city of LEGOs?\r\n							<br/>\r\nWould you like to leverage your love of LEGOs to learn about critical real-life lessons and strategies?<br/>\r\nThen, join us for one or two weeks of fun and responsibility at our very popular Kidizens Summer Camps at one of our locations.\r\n</b></p>\r\n							<p>Another successful and creative round of Summer Camps has come to a close after the creation of over 150 thriving metropolises buzzing with the hustle and bustle of city life.</p>\r\n							<p>\r\n								Please check out of Fall and Winter Camps and our Fall Programs if you are interested in joining our journey as Kidizens.\r\n							</p>\r\n							<p>Registration for next years Summer Camp program opens November 21st 2016.</p>\r\n							<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vcd35Y-Y5_E" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n', 'LEGO Summer Camps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-24 09:37:44', '2016-11-24 09:37:44', '', 36, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2016/11/24/36-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
