(533, 1, '2017-01-12 13:21:17', '2017-01-12 13:21:17', ' <h4 class="title"> </h4>\n							<br/><br/>\n                            <p>This is an excellent way to introduce budding builders to the fundamentals of simple machines concepts while building teamwork and communication skills. Young students will work in groups and build fun LEGO projects – things they see, use and experience everyday; things that move, rotate, pull/push, make sounds or light up. In this fun learning environment, the Kinderzens will discover many physical science models such as gears, pulleys, levers, wheels and axles through observation and building – without realizing that they are learning about simple machines!</p>\n							<div class="listing">\n							<p><b>Los Altos Classes (Serving Palo Alto, Los Altos and Mountain View areas):</b></p>\n							<p>Wednesday      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  1:15 PM – 2:45 PM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;      Kinderzens<br/>\n								Friday                   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    3:45 PM – 5:15 PM  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Kinderzens\n							</p>\n							<a href="#" class="register-button">Register</a>\n							</div>\n							<div class="listing">\n							<p><b>Belmont Classes (Serving Belmont, San Carlos, San Mateo, Foster City and Redwood City areas):</b></p>\n							<p>Tuesday      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  1:15 PM – 2:45 PM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;      Kinderzens\n							</p>\n							<a href="#" class="register-button">Register</a>\n							</div>\n', 'Kinderzens', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '44-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-01-12 13:21:17', '2017-01-12 13:21:17', '', 44, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2017/01/12/44-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
