(574, 1, '2017-01-27 12:30:35', '2017-01-27 12:30:35', '<h4 class="title">Kidizens Lego Summer Camps for the Bay Area</h4>\r\n<p><b>Would your child like to build and be the Mayor of an entire city of LEGOs?\r\n							<br/>\r\nWould you like your child to leverage  their love of LEGOs to learn critical 21st century skills and strategies?\r\n</b></p>\r\n<p><b>Have your child join us for one to two weeks of fun and (leadership, growth, collaboration?) at our very popular Kidizens Summer Camps in Los Altos, Belmont and soon to be announced new locations in Fremont, Los Gatos, Palo Alto, Burlingame, and Palo Alto! \r\n</b></p>\r\n<h5>ABOUT US</h5>\r\n<p><b>Camps are suitable for grades K-6. They run from 9am-3pm (with an extended care till 5pm option.) There’s a different theme every week. Please scroll down for themes, dates and (do you want to have a Typical Day Schedule?). </b></p>\r\n							<p>At Kidizens, children’s passion and creativity are nurtured and engaged to become good (thoughtful?) citizens and future leaders, one LEGO brick at a time.  During our excitement-packed Bay Area LEGO Summer Camps kids plan and create their own small LEGO civilization. As active participants, kids:\r\n</p>\r\n<ul class="summer_list">\r\n<li>Serve as a Co-Mayor for a week </li>\r\n<li>Manage the economy, residents and their needs</li>\r\n<li>Create city infrastructure to handle the unexpected (floods, fire, crime, sewer line breaks etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Deal with issues in an age-appropriate manner</li>\r\n<li>Develop public policy platform and campaign</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In our fast-paced dynamic environment, students are carefully and positively guided. They will have fun and:</p>\r\n<ul class="summer_list">\r\n<li>Develop leadership and interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Role play as responsible leader</li>\r\n<li>Wear many hats</li>\r\n<li>Think out of the box and on their feet</li>\r\n<li>Problem-solve and make decisions</li>\r\n<li>Speak publicly </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>SEE US IN ACTION</h5>\r\n<div class="separation"><p>Get a glimpse of our younger Mayors (Ages 6-9) in action!</p>\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/XgJ4luELRrs" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="separation">\r\n<p>Los Legos, a wonderful city built by our Co-<b>Mayos</b> (Ages 9-11). </p>\r\n							<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vcd35Y-Y5_E" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Here’s an election campaign ad from our 2-week Co-Mayors responding to a prominent industrialist opponent candidate!</p>\r\n<div class="separation">\r\n<p>Also, watch this testimonial video from one of our past our summer camp sessions where our students and LEGO city mayors met the real mayor of Palo Alto, Sid Espinosa, and hear his impressions of Kidizens.</p>\r\n<iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/GWCh1FIN6Kc" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0"></iframe>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Our summer camps have received tremendous parent endorsements with glowing reviews and have become increasingly popular. Many kids returned for a 2nd and a 3rd year to our camps this past summer. For kids who have experienced the thrill of a serving as mayors past summers, we have added many new themes and elements to make the camps even more exciting and super fun.</p>\r\n<h5>Highlights:</h5>\r\n<div class="listing">\r\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> 1-week camps suitable for grades K-3 and for grades 3-6</h6>\r\n<p>separately and partnered age-appropriately – older kids building their own cities and presented with more complex challenges and problem solving opportunities.</p>\r\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> 2-week camps for grades 3-6 only</h6>\r\n<p>experience which allows kids to solve many complex challenges, dig deeper for city solutions and develop an entire mayoral campaign towards the election for a 2nd term against a real opponent.</p>\r\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> A new focus on role-play</h6>\r\n<p>Children will have an opportunity to choose a city role, undergo job training, wear the ‘new hat’ (and appropriate uniform) and role play during the week to perform key tasks for that job.</p>\r\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Immerse yourself in a different theme/goal every week</h6>\r\n<p>such as Explorers, Gold Rush, Space Crusaders, Cities of Future, Back to the Medieval Times. Minecraft and many more….</p>\r\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> For kids that love Robotics</h6>\r\n<p>there will be opportunities to build add city-related Robotic elements (motorized cars, signs, doors, toll booths, etc.) to make our cities animated and come alive!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h6><b>2017 Bay Area LEGO Summer Camps (new locations to be announced soon):</b></h6>\r\n<h6><b>I. 1-Week camp options</b></h6>\r\n<div class="listing">\r\n<p><b>A. Camps Offered at Los Altos location:</b></p>\r\n<p>4546 El Camino Real, Suite B9, Los Altos, CA\r\n(At the Intersection of El Camino Real and San Antonio Road)</p>\r\n<p><b>June 5th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 12th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 19th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 26th\r\nJuly 3rd* &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 10th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 17th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 24th \r\nJuly 31st &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;August 7th</b></p>\r\n<p><b>For Los Altos 1-Week Summer Camps, Register Here:</b></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/376" class="register-button" target="_blank">Register</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="listing">\r\n<p><b>B. Camps Offered at Belmont location:</b></p>\r\n<p>1338 El Camino Real, Belmont CA</p>\r\n<p><b>June 19th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 26th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 3rd* &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 10th\r\nJuly 1th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 18th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 25th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;August 1st\r\nAugust 8th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;August 15th</b></p>\r\n<p><b>For Belmont 1-Week Summer Camps, Register Here:</b></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/376" class="register-button" target="_blank">Register</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h6><b>II. Two-week Options</b></h6>\r\n<div class="listing">\r\n<p>(currently offered at the Kidizens Los Altos location only)</p>\r\n<p><b>June 12th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 26th* &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 10th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 24th  \r\n</b></p>\r\n<p><b>For Los Altos 2-Week Summer Camps, Register Here:</b></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/376" class="register-button" target="_blank">Register</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="listing">\r\n<p><b>A few things to note: </b></p>\r\n<p>*Aftercare provided until 5pm at additional cost\r\n*Daily walks to a nearby park for lunch and city-related, civic games\r\n*Healthy Snacks provided morning and afternoon\r\n*Free lunch provided on Wednesdays; Please bring easy-to-carry, nut-free lunch all other days.\r\n*The 1-week camp for the week of July 3rd runs only 4 days and the 2-week camp for the week of June 28th runs only 9 days, with no camp on July 4th. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Please email info@kidzzinc.com if you have any questions pertaining to any of the summer camps. </p>\r\n<p><b>Pricing:</b> See our Pricing Page for more details</p>\r\n<p>Our camps offer a great opportunity for high-schoolers and middle-schoolers. Please click here for more information relating to Kidizens Volunteer and Intern opportunities this summer.</p>', 'LEGO Summer Camps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-27 12:30:35', '2017-01-27 12:30:35', '', 36, 'http://anvinfosystem.com/project/kid/2017/01/27/36-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
