(664, 1, '2017-02-15 13:40:15', '2017-02-15 13:40:15', '<br><br>\n							<h4 class="title">Kidizens Lego Summer Camps for the Bay Area</h4>\n<p class="highlighter"><b>Would you like to build and be the Mayor of an entire city of LEGOs?\n							<br>	<br>\nWould you like to leverage your love of LEGOs to learn critical real-life lessons and strategies?\n</b></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/1307" class="register-button" target="_blank" style="float:right;">Cancellation Policy</a></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><b>Join us for one to two weeks of fun and responsibility at our very popular Kidizens Summer Camps at any one of our locations, in Los Altos, Belmont and Saratoga!\n\nStay tuned as we continue to announce many new locations throughout the Bay area (in Los Gatos, Fremont, San Jose) this summer!\n</b></p>\n<p><b>Kidizens</b> inspires students to become good citizens and future leaders, one LEGO brick at a time. The Kidizens Summer Program includes intensive action and excitement-packed sessions, where children create their own small civilization built with LEGOs and serve as Co-Mayors for a week. The Co-Mayors manage the economy, the residents and their needs, city departments and services and deal with unexpected problems and situations in an age-appropriate manner. In a fast-paced dynamic environment, the kids develop leadership and interpersonal skills while dealing with natural disasters, resident problems and financial crises.\n\nThis is a rare opportunity for kids to role play as responsible leaders in addition to wearing many other hats – think out of the box and on their feet, problem solve and come to decisions in a fast, action-packed, exciting environment. They also learn how to develop a public policy platform and campaign as well as address residents through speeches against a real opponent.</p>\n<h5>Highlights:</h5>\n<div class="listing">\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> 1-week camps suitable for grades K-3 and for grades 3-6</h6>\n<p>grouped separately and partnered age-appropriately – older kids building their own cities and presented with more complex challenges and problem solving opportunities.</p>\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> 2-week camps for grades 3-6 only</h6>\n<p>A highly immersive and in-depth experience which allows kids to solve many complex challenges, dig deeper for city solutions and develop an entire mayoral campaign towards the election for a 2nd term against a real opponent.</p>\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> A new focus on role-play</h6>\n<p>Children will have an opportunity to choose a city role, undergo job training, wear the ‘new hat’ (and appropriate associated accessories) and role play during the week to perform key tasks for that job.</p>\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Immerse in a different theme/goal every week</h6>\n<p>such as Explorers, Gold Rush, Space Crusaders, Cities of Future, Back to the Medieval Times. Minecraft and many more….</p>\n<h6><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> For kids that love Robotics</h6>\n<p>there will be opportunities to build add city-related Robotic elements (motorized cars, signs, doors, toll booths, etc.) to make our cities animated and come alive!</p>\n</div>\n<h6><b>2017 Bay Area LEGO Summer Camps</b></h6>\n<h6><b>I. 1-Week camp options</b></h6>\n<div class="listing">\n<p><b>A. Camps Offered at Los Altos location:</b></p>\n<p>4546 El Camino Real, Suite B9, Los Altos, CA\n(At the Intersection of El Camino Real and San Antonio Road)</p>\n<p><b>June 5th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 12th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 19th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 26th<br>\nJuly 3rd* &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 10th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 17th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 24th <br>\nJuly 31st &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;August 7th</b></p>\n<p><b>For Los Altos 1-Week Summer Camps, Register Here:</b></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/1307" class="register-button" target="_blank">Register</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="listing">\n<p><b>B. Camps Offered at Belmont location:</b></p>\n<p>1338 El Camino Real, Belmont CA</p>\n<p><b>June 19th   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; June 26th   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 3rd* &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 10th<br>\nJuly 17th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 24th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 31th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;August 7th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;August 14th<br>\nAugust 8th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;August 15th</b></p>\n<p><b>For Belmont 1-Week Summer Camps, Register Here:</b></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/1306" class="register-button" target="_blank">Register</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="listing">\n<p><b>C. Camps Offered at Menlo Park:</b></p>\n<p>Offered at Laurel Upper Campus, 275 Elliot Drive, Menlo Park, CA</p>\n<p><b>June 19th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 26th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 10th<br>\nJuly 17th &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 24th</b></p>\n<p><b>For Menlo Park 1-Week Summer Camps, Register Here:</b></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/1483" class="register-button" target="_blank">Register</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="listing">\n<p><b>D. Camps Offered at Palo Alto:</b></p>\n<p>Offered at Walter Hays School, 1525 Middlefield Rd, Palo Alto, CA</p>\n<p><b>June 12th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 19th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 26th<br>\nJuly 10nh &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 17th</b></p>\n<p><b>For Palo Alto 1-Week Summer Camps, Register Here: </b></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/1441" class="register-button" target="_blank">Register</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="listing">\n<p><b>E. Camps Offered at Los Gatos:</b></p>\n<p>Offered at Mulberry School, 220 Belgatos Rd, Los Gatos, CA</p>\n<p><b>June 12th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 19th  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;June 26th<br>\nJuly 10nh &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;July 17th</b></p>\n<p><b>For Mulberry School, Los Gatos 1-Week Summer Camps, Register Here:  </b></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.activityhero.com/widgets/1441" class="register-button" target="_blank">Register</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="listing">\n<p><b>F. 